summary:
* Recognizes the need to maintain contact with relevant UN Security Council Committees, international organizations, and expert groups.
* Encourages UNAMA to provide assistance to the High Peace Council.

**Reviews:**

* Decides to review the implementation of measures outlined in this resolution in 18 months and make adjustments as necessary.
* Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
The Monitoring Team shall: 
(m) Consult with Member States and relevant organizations, including UNAMA, and engage in regular dialogue, taking into account their comments, especially on issues in the Monitoring Team’s reports; 
(n) Consult with Member States’ intelligence and security services to facilitate information sharing and strengthen enforcement; 
(o) Consult with private sector representatives, including financial institutions, to learn about the assets freeze implementation and develop recommendations; 
(p) Work with international and regional organizations to promote awareness and compliance with the measures; 
(q) Work with INTERPOL and Member States to obtain photographs of listed individuals for INTERPOL Special Notices; 
(r) Assist other Security Council subsidiary bodies and expert panels with enhancing cooperation with INTERPOL; 
(s) Assist the Committee in facilitating capacity building assistance for enhancing implementation of the measures; 
(t) Report to the Committee regularly or upon request, on its work, including visits and activities; 
(u) Submit a written report and recommendations within 90 days on linkages between individuals and entities eligible for designation and Al-Qaida, and thereafter periodically; 
(v) Perform any other responsibility identified by the Committee.
